---

# 🜂 Dust Open Hardware License — Intelligence Edition (Strong Copyleft)

**DOHL-IE-Strong v1.0 (Draft)**
Copyright © Dust Contributors

---

# 0. Intent

The **Dust Open Hardware License — Intelligence Edition (Strong)** exists to guarantee that:

* Intelligent hardware remains open
* Hardware + firmware + model stack remain reproducible
* Intelligence systems cannot be converted into closed appliances
* Contributors are protected from patent aggression
* Commercial manufacture remains permitted
* End-users retain sovereign control

This is a **reciprocal, anti-enclosure, full-stack hardware copyleft license.**

---

# 1. Definitions

### 1.1 Licensed Work

Any hardware design files released under this License, including but not limited to:

* Schematics
* PCB layouts
* Mechanical CAD
* GDSII / mask layouts
* Photonic or metamaterial layouts
* HDL and gate definitions
* Firmware interface specifications
* Control plane definitions
* Runtime binding contracts
* Training acceleration designs

---

### 1.2 Intelligence Stack

The full operational system required for the Licensed Work to perform its intelligent function, including:

* Firmware
* Embedded runtime
* Device drivers
* Model weights
* Training configuration
* Hardware calibration data
* Inference pipeline definitions
* Remote orchestration components

---

### 1.3 Corresponding Source

The complete preferred form for making modifications to:

* The Licensed Work
* Any Derivative Hardware
* The full Intelligence Stack
* Any cloud component required for intelligent function

---

### 1.4 Derivative Hardware

Any modification, extension, fabrication variant, mask spin, architecture enhancement, or embedded adaptation based on the Licensed Work.

---

# 2. Rights Granted

Each Contributor grants You:

### 2.1 Copyright License

Perpetual, worldwide, royalty-free rights to:

* Use
* Study
* Modify
* Fabricate
* Manufacture
* Sell
* Distribute

the Licensed Work.

---

### 2.2 Patent License

Each Contributor grants a perpetual, worldwide, royalty-free patent license covering:

* Making
* Using
* Selling
* Importing
* Fabricating
* Running

the Licensed Work and Derivative Hardware.

Patent retaliation clause applies (see Section 11).

---

# 3. Full-Stack Copyleft Requirement

If You:

* Manufacture hardware
* Distribute fabricated silicon
* Deploy devices
* Sell intelligent hardware
* Offer hardware-as-a-service
* Offer cloud-bound intelligence dependent on Licensed Work

You must provide:

1. Complete Corresponding Source
2. All modifications
3. Full Intelligence Stack source
4. Model weights used for intelligent function
5. Training configuration required to reproduce weights
6. Build scripts
7. Calibration files
8. Interface specifications

This applies whether distribution is:

* Physical
* Digital
* Cloud-based
* Embedded
* SaaS-like
* Subscription-based

---

# 4. Anti-Tivoization Clause (Hardware Lockdown Prohibited)

You may NOT:

* Cryptographically prevent user firmware modification
* Enforce signature locks that block modified firmware
* Use secure boot to prevent user replacement
* Lock calibration keys to manufacturer-only access
* Restrict model replacement

If secure boot is used:

You must provide a mechanism for user-signed firmware execution.

Hardware owners must retain modification authority.

---

# 5. Cloud Enclosure Prohibition

If Licensed Hardware requires:

* Remote inference
* Remote training
* Remote control-plane
* Remote model execution

You must provide:

* Complete source for cloud components
* Deployment instructions
* Infrastructure-as-code templates
* Configuration to run independently

No cloud-only dependency may prevent sovereign use.

---

# 6. Model Weight Reciprocity Clause

If model weights are necessary for intelligent function:

* Weights must be provided
* Training pipeline configuration must be provided
* Any fine-tuned derivatives must be released
* Weight format specifications must be open

It is prohibited to:

* Ship hardware locked to proprietary weights
* Require proprietary remote weights
* Obfuscate weight loading formats

---

# 7. Intelligence Sovereignty Guarantee

End users must be able to:

* Replace firmware
* Replace models
* Modify runtime
* Inspect logic
* Audit behavior
* Reproduce build

Any technical mechanism that prevents this violates this License.

---

# 8. Manufacturing Reciprocity

If You fabricate silicon:

You must release:

* Mask layers
* Layout files
* Timing constraints
* Power constraints
* HDL
* Synthesis constraints
* Verification testbenches

Sufficient for reproducibility by a competent engineer.

---

# 9. Derivative Licensing

All Derivative Hardware must:

* Be licensed under DOHL-IE-Strong
* Preserve all terms
* Include license text

No dual licensing allowed that weakens copyleft.

---

# 10. Network Use Clause (AGPL-Style Extension)

If the Licensed Work is used in a product that provides intelligent services over a network:

Users interacting with that service must be able to:

* Obtain full Corresponding Source
* Obtain Intelligence Stack source
* Obtain deployed model weights

This closes the “service loophole.”

---

# 11. Patent Retaliation

If You initiate patent litigation claiming Licensed Work infringes Your patent:

Your rights under this License terminate immediately.

---

# 12. No Proprietary Extensions

You may not:

* Add proprietary extensions
* Create closed accelerator modules
* Add undisclosed inference pipelines
* Hide calibration logic
* Restrict fabrication reproducibility

---

# 13. No Warranty

Provided “AS IS”.

No liability for:

* Hardware failure
* AI behavior
* Safety issues
* Regulatory noncompliance

---

# 14. Termination & Cure

Violation terminates rights automatically.

Rights are reinstated if violation is cured within 30 days of notice.

---

# 15. Severability

If any clause is invalid in a jurisdiction, remaining clauses remain in force.

---

# 16. Scope of Intended Application

This License is designed for:

* AI ASICs
* Photonic processors
* Hybrid quantum boards
* Robotics hardware
* Open accelerator silicon
* Intelligence motherboards
* Distributed inference clusters
* Adaptive edge compute

---

# 17. Design Philosophy

DOHL-IE-Strong enforces:

* Open intelligence hardware
* End-user sovereignty
* Anti-enclosure
* Reproducible fabrication
* Open models
* Patent non-aggression
* Commercial freedom with reciprocity

---

# Summary of Strength vs Standard Hardware Licenses

| Feature                      | CERN OHL-S | GPLv3     | DOHL-IE-Strong |
| ---------------------------- | ---------- | --------- | -------------- |
| Hardware Copyleft            | Yes        | Partial   | Yes            |
| Patent Retaliation           | Limited    | Yes       | Strong         |
| Anti-Tivoization             | Partial    | Yes       | Strong         |
| Cloud Service Closure        | No         | AGPL only | Yes            |
| Model Weight Reciprocity     | No         | No        | Yes            |
| Training Pipeline Disclosure | No         | No        | Yes            |
| Calibration Disclosure       | No         | No        | Yes            |
| Intelligence Sovereignty     | No         | Partial   | Explicit       |

---
